Caspian tern
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a large red-billed tern, Sterna caspia, with black cap and forked tail (also called taranui); found on the New Zealand coast and widely elsewhere.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
